  <original-body>Some gems apparently are packed oddly, with (for example) all files set to read-only. (Hoe is one - thanks ssoroka!)

This causes problems, as the 2.2 gem unpack code will unpack dependencies more than once.

The attached patch is more careful with dependencies; it will only unpack each gem *once*. This should fix issues that some users have been having with gems:unpack:dependencies.</original-body>
